arity markers and serial verb constructions. Literary genres of the region and related art forms such as songs and the symbolic sand drawings are discussed in the final chapter. The grammar will be especially relevant to readers with an interest in Oceanic languages, general typology and theoretical linguistics as well as those with a broader interest in the region.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mrz 2022) 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aLanguage Description.  aLanguage Documentation.  aOceanic Languages.1 aBarth, Roderich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDanz, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDienstbeck, Stefan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrözinger, Elisabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHauser, Linus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJamme, Christoph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKorsch, Dietrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKörtner, Ulrich H. J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMurrmann-Kahl, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchüßler, Werner, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSturm, Erdmann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb0 cprintz978311034259840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311076631840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110766318423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110766318/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-all